<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idcad3dca5-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70" identifier="/us/usc/t49/s5908"><num value="5908">§ 5908.</num><heading> Relationship to other laws</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Nothing in this chapter affects—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idcad3dca6-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70" identifier="/us/usc/t49/s5908/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> chapter 51 (relating to transportation of hazardous material) or the regulations promulgated under that chapter; or</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idcad3dca7-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70" identifier="/us/usc/t49/s5908/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> any State highway weight or size law or regulation applicable to tractor-trailer combinations.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="idcad3dca8-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/104/291/tII/s209/a">Pub. L. 104–291, title II, § 209(a)</ref>, <date date="1996-10-11">Oct. 11, 1996</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/110/3458">110 Stat. 3458</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
